Permissions : There are 3 types permissions 
1. Use Permission
2. Group permission
3. Other permission

rwx
r: read permission
w: write permission
x: execute permission
a: all permission

 Note If first character is d then it is directort
If first character is - then it is file


for check permission ls -l

To change permission of file we need to login as root user
for that su command use
eg. su

Task1: Create file
cat> saroj.txt
or touch file1.txt
Task2: Modify Permission

chmod +permission
chmod a+rwx  filename.txt
eg. chmod  a+rwx saroj.txt
This command will provide all permission to saroj 
chmod u+ rw
user only have read write permission
chmod u+x file1.txt


Task3: Change ownership
chown 
sudo chown ram saroj.txt

Task4: Test access
ls -l filename
ls -l saroj.txt








